site_name_pinyin: Name of building complex in pinyin romanization, if differentiated by placename, placename should be included in this category
site_name2_traditional: Name of building complex in traditional characters
site_name3_simplified: Name of building complex in simplified characters
building_name_pinyin: Name of individual structure; this refers to a building within a larger building complex; capitalized only if proper name
building_name2_traditional: Name of individual structure in traditional characters
building_name3_simplified: Name of individual strucutre in simplified characters
building_name_in_site: Name of individual structure within a building complex. This category is most important when searching for a general structure carrying a common name (e.g. main hall, Daxiongbao Hall, etc.) so that the primary differentiating feature, and thus most common search term, is the name of the complex rather than the name of the building. Map this column to building in Flickr.
alternate building_name_pinyin: This column is used to include alternate names for temple complexes; especially useful for building complexes where their names are differentiated primarily by placename (town, province, etc.)
